   <font class="ArticleSource"><big>News Roundup:</big></font>
   <font class="ArticleHead"><big>You Feel a Healing Touch</big></font>
   <font class="ArticleAuthorLight">&nbsp;filed by </font><font class="ArticleAuthor">Csenicier</font>
   <div align="right">
   <font class="ArticleTime">07/15/2002 11:43 AM CDT &nbsp;&nbsp; 10 Comments</font>
   <div align="left">
   <font class="ArticleText"><BIG>Healing Penalty Removed on Test</BIG><p>An <a href="http://forums.interealms.com/ranger/showthread.php?s=5cd4873a8ad294d9946ee78432134902&amp;threadid=5975">interesting thread</a> has surfaced on the <a href="http://forums.interealms.com/ranger/index.php?s=5cd4873a8ad294d9946ee78432134902">Ranger's Glade</a> claiming that the penalty levied to direct heals cast by non-clerics has been removed on the Test server.<p>Since EQ's infancy, direct or instant heals cast by non clerics have suffered a 10% penalty.  A Greater Heal cast by a Druid, for example, would heal 270 points despite the fact that Greater Heal is listed as a 300 point heal (in the spdat file).  Clerics already receive a 5% bonus to damage healed by their direct heals.<p>What motivates the change at this point?  Certainly Druids and Shamans have been making noise about the inadequacy of their healing powers.  This will give them a bit of a boost in that area.  Also a Druid or Shaman is much more inclined to actually use a direct heal while a Cleric makes his money with Complete Heal and efficient heals over time such as Celestial Elixir.<p>Clerics <a href="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/Forum1/HTML/008895.html">hardly seemed threatened</a> by the news.  And <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showMessageRange?topicID=16014.topic&amp;start=1&amp;stop=20">other classes</a> are welcoming the change.<p><BIG>New Planes of Power Prologue</BIG><p>The <a href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/power/index.jsp">Planes of Power</a> site has been updated.  It now shows the entry to the Plane of Tranquility opening outside the temple of Quellious in Erudin.  Make sure to read the <a href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/power/prologue.jsp">prologue</a> surrounding these new mystical events. Pearce and crew promise many more PoP site updates in the weeks ahead.<p><BIG>Scheduled Maintenance</BIG><p><B>On Tuesday, July 16th, between the hours of 3AM and 6AM PDT, (11AM-2PM GMT), network maintenance will be performed that could lead to some connectivity issues for some customers.<p>The following servers will be affected:<br>Erollisi Marr, Cazic Thule, Brell Serilis, The Rathe, Lanys T'vyl, Torvonnilous, Tunare, Quellious, Xegony, Prexus, Bertoxxulous, Rallos Zek, Veeshan, Rodcet Nife, Karana, The Nameless, Mithaniel Marr, Morell Thule, The Seventh Hammer, Saryrn, Sullon Zek<p>The EverQuest Operations Team</B><p>Finally.  All this up-time was really making me nervous.<p><BIG>Fayding Away</BIG><p>The Magician's Tower brings news of a <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showMessage?topicID=5693.topic">new NPC</a> in the Firepot Room of Timorous Deep.  The purpose of this NPC it seems is to warn travelers of the mighty water dragon - presumably Faydedar.<p>The Firepot room has been a popular bind location for caster since it was re-enabled a few weeks back, so why is the warning necessary now?  Faydedar (the non-triggered version) has had problem pathing since Kunark opened for business.  Faydedar would pass by an unfriendly monk NPC and promptly become fish food.  Perhaps this pathing has been corrected, greatly increasing Faydedar's life expectancy.  Or perhaps Verant is discouraging the use of the Firepot transport system for other reasons--such as the promised transportation system in PoP.  Who knows.<p><BIG>Alone But Not Afraid</BIG><p>Tawanos Gunn has posted a <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=18479.topic">guide</a> on <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation">Graffe's</a> to one of his favorite solo spots: The Plane of Fear.  That's right.  Breaking and clearing PoF short of the boss mobs (of course).  It's an interesting read and really demonstrates the power of the modern Wizard.  Anyone who remembers 30+ person wipe-outs trying to break Fear will really appreciate this accomplishment.</font>
  </td>
 </tr>
